definition: to enter/to go into/to join/to become a member of/to confirm or agree with/abbr. for 入聲|入声[ru4 sheng1]
large place used for a specific purpose/stage/scene (of a play)/classifier for sporting or recreational activities/classifier for number of exams
threshing floor/classifier for events and happenings: spell, episode, bout

sentences.english: There are videos and pictures up of my entrance at all of the poker sites.
sentences.chinese: 很多網站都有這個入場式的錄像和照片。

sentences.english: This is a unique "water entrance ceremony."
sentences.chinese: 這是一場別開生面的“水上入場式”。

sentences.english: Do you remember the last Olympics in Athens?
sentences.chinese: 奧運會入場式上，東道國隊總是最後出場。
